choices.text:
generally being seriously too fucking hot on the train (Helsinki publicly owns and runs the trains), and it is almost impossible to dress for three seasons. It was seriously above 30*C yesterday and only partly overcast/slightly windy. However, in winter, it can be 0* C during the day and in -20*C at night with thick snow and cold gusts of wind… Or I have also tried -23,5*C four years ago, which was hell (it was far, far worse than -36, during winter, bushes felt like there was a river running int them and I had maybe one slight bruise on my leg for the rest of the year). But yeah, you ca barely breath or see anywhere if it is that bad. I also know depression is one of the biggest populations in Finland, though I do not know about minorities (this factivist told me). Gender roles affect me more, considering my work as a designer greatly depends on attention to slim measured clothing… It’s such an extense multi leveled cultural fuck up.

And yeah, it’s pretty unknown for most people.

I wouldn’t worry about being able to reply to my own comments too much.

You live in Finland? Like many Swedes I had suspicions about this because of this song… You’re allowed to use 4GB of data per month for about $18.exchange rates but that’s not very generous… The data stuff does seem somewhat idiotic when there is free WiFi nearly everywhere
